00:36:51,330 --> 00:36:54,010
You're giving this house to Gary?

799
00:36:55,070 --> 00:36:57,580
[CRYING]

800
00:36:59,040 --> 00:37:00,628
Bloody hell, that was
supposed to make you happy.

801
00:37:00,630 --> 00:37:01,950
Not insufferable.

802
00:37:01,960 --> 00:37:04,600
I promise to take great care
of this place, you know?

803
00:37:04,610 --> 00:37:07,540
I'll feed the hellhounds, I'll vacuum...

804
00:37:07,550 --> 00:37:10,349
You know, why don't we
talk about what you had

805
00:37:10,350 --> 00:37:12,520
on your bucket list, eh, mate?

806
00:37:12,530 --> 00:37:13,889
- Really?
- Yeah.

807
00:37:13,890 --> 00:37:16,059
Give me something meaningful, eh?

808
00:37:16,060 --> 00:37:21,810
Well, eventually I...

809
00:37:21,820 --> 00:37:24,820
plan on asking Nora to marry me.

810
00:37:26,740 --> 00:37:28,570
Can I be your flower boy?

811
00:37:29,660 --> 00:37:33,740
Oh, that's very sweet, Gary.
Odd but very sweet.

812
00:37:33,750 --> 00:37:36,749
Why haven't you asked her yet, Big Man?

813
00:37:36,750 --> 00:37:40,640
I've been engaged twice before.

814
00:37:40,650 --> 00:37:43,839
Both times didn't end as I had hoped.

815
00:37:43,840 --> 00:37:49,009
You know, life, it is too short
to dillydally, Raymond.

816
00:37:49,010 --> 00:37:50,819
I know you... you can
take that from a man

817
00:37:50,820 --> 00:37:54,960
who has nothing but regrets.

818
00:37:54,970 --> 00:37:58,430
So if you love that witch,

819
00:37:58,440 --> 00:38:00,480
you bloody will marry her, right?

820
00:38:02,900 --> 00:38:05,440
[COUGHS]

821
00:38:05,450 --> 00:38:06,888
No, no, no. I'm all
right, I'm all right.

822
00:38:06,890 --> 00:38:09,240
[SNIFFLES] Now how about a toast, eh?

823
00:38:10,570 --> 00:38:12,820
Okay.

824
00:38:12,830 --> 00:38:15,380
No, with this.

825
00:38:15,390 --> 00:38:19,340
Oh, of all the ways that
I'd thought I'd go,

826
00:38:19,350 --> 00:38:24,190
decapitated by a demon,
eviscerated by an elemental,

827
00:38:24,200 --> 00:38:26,970
I wouldn't have picked being
at home with my mates.

828
00:38:27,970 --> 00:38:29,800
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

829
00:38:29,810 --> 00:38:31,840
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

830
00:38:41,150 --> 00:38:43,309
[SIGHS]

831
00:38:43,310 --> 00:38:45,920
[COUGHING]

832
00:38:47,690 --> 00:38:49,280
[SIGHS]

833
00:38:49,290 --> 00:38:52,660
You know, I just wish I
had more time with you...

834
00:38:52,670 --> 00:38:54,510
lovely idiots.

835
00:38:54,520 --> 00:38:57,619
Well, you're not dead yet, John.

836
00:38:57,620 --> 00:39:00,159
No, but I will be momentarily.

837
00:39:00,160 --> 00:39:03,490
[FOREBODING MUSIC]

838
00:39:03,500 --> 00:39:05,379
♪ ♪

839
00:39:05,380 --> 00:39:06,959
[CHUCKLES]

840
00:39:06,960 --> 00:39:09,830
John Constantine.

841
00:39:09,840 --> 00:39:12,280
He always goes out on his own terms.

842
00:39:12,290 --> 00:39:13,299
[GRUNTS]

843
00:39:13,300 --> 00:39:14,470
John?

844
00:39:17,080 --> 00:39:20,229
[EERIE MUSIC]

845
00:39:20,230 --> 00:39:22,599
Couldn't wait to see me, John.

846
00:39:22,600 --> 00:39:25,780
60 seconds and you're dead.

847
00:39:25,790 --> 00:39:27,820
[SIGHS]

848
00:39:27,830 --> 00:39:29,360
Poison does that.

849
00:39:33,160 --> 00:39:37,230
It was the same poison your
mother used to kill herself.

850
00:39:37,240 --> 00:39:40,369
You won't change my mind.

851
00:39:40,370 --> 00:39:43,420
I'm not trying to.

852
00:39:43,430 --> 00:39:46,440
I just want you know that...

853
00:39:46,450 --> 00:39:49,770
even though you gave up on her,

854
00:39:49,780 --> 00:39:51,840
your mum never gave up on you.

855
00:39:53,680 --> 00:39:55,280
[COUGHS AND GROANS]

856
00:39:55,290 --> 00:39:57,620
[SIGHS]

857
00:39:58,870 --> 00:40:03,990
♪ Are you going to Scarborough Fair ♪

858
00:40:04,000 --> 00:40:08,770
♪ Parsley, sage, rosemary, and thyme ♪

859
00:40:08,780 --> 00:40:11,029
- ♪ Remember me ♪
- Stop.

860
00:40:11,030 --> 00:40:14,530
♪ To one who lives there ♪

861
00:40:14,540 --> 00:40:15,699
♪ For once ♪

862
00:40:15,700 --> 00:40:16,900
BOTH: ♪ She was ♪

863
00:40:16,910 --> 00:40:19,000
♪ A true love of mine ♪

864
00:40:19,010 --> 00:40:21,469
That was our song.

865
00:40:21,470 --> 00:40:23,970
Aye, it was.

866
00:40:23,980 --> 00:40:26,830
But she sang it to me first.

867
00:40:30,130 --> 00:40:33,469
You can really bring her back?

868
00:40:33,470 --> 00:40:36,130
[COUGHS]

869
00:40:36,140 --> 00:40:37,389
Answer me.

870
00:40:37,390 --> 00:40:39,350
I can fix everything.

871
00:40:42,590 --> 00:40:44,099
[UPBEAT MUSIC]

872
00:40:44,100 --> 00:40:47,269
[GROANING]

873
00:40:47,270 --> 00:40:52,900
♪ ♪

874
00:40:52,910 --> 00:40:54,150
I'm glad that hurt.

875
00:40:56,710 --> 00:40:57,989
Tick tock, John.

876
00:40:57,990 --> 00:41:02,080
I can kill you anytime I want.

877
00:41:04,290 --> 00:41:06,650
- [GASPING]
- Oh, oh, my God!

878
00:41:06,660 --> 00:41:09,440
- I can't take this anymore.
- How are you alive?

879
00:41:09,450 --> 00:41:11,799
Astra, she reconsidered.

880
00:41:11,800 --> 00:41:13,680
She reconsidered, she reconsidered.

881
00:41:13,690 --> 00:41:15,799
She reconsidered. She reconsidered!

882
00:41:15,800 --> 00:41:18,080
Oh, I can't bloody believe it.

883
00:41:18,090 --> 00:41:19,509
I'm back in the game. Oh, Bully.

884
00:41:19,510 --> 00:41:22,260
Bully, Bully, Bully. Bully, I love you!

885
00:41:22,270 --> 00:41:24,170
Bully, Bully, Bully, Bully, Bully.

886
00:41:24,180 --> 00:41:26,809
Yes, I can't believe she
bloody reconsidered!

887
00:41:26,810 --> 00:41:30,040
Mwah! I feel like a new man.

888
00:41:30,050 --> 00:41:31,540
Ah, yeah.

889
00:41:31,550 --> 00:41:33,780
I can't believe I was gonna
leave my house to you.

890
00:41:33,790 --> 00:41:35,970
- What?
- Here, give me that will.

